dataset.description: In 2020, voter-approved Measure B created a new independent Commission on Police Practices (CPP) that replaced the Community Review Board on Police Practices (CRB). The CPP independently investigates officer-involved shootings, in-custody deaths, & other significant incidents in a process that is transparent and accountable to the community. The CPP also evaluates SDPD policies, practices, training, and protocols. This dataset includes all cases the CPP reviewed and closed out since the beginning of FY 2019.
dataset.title: Complaints Evaluated by the Commission on Police Practices

dataset.description: Actions an officer took toward a person stopped by the San Diego Police Department. dataset.title: RIPA police stop data - gender of persons stopped
